            "last_activity_date": 1432226006,
            "creation_date": 1432226006,
            "body": "<p>Use <code>readLine()<\/code> and then split the read String with <code>split(\" \")<\/code>.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 30379504,
            "question_id": 30379401
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/5n0wW.png?s=256",
                "account_id": 6129637,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 4780330,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4780330/mlavrentyev",
                "reputation": 1970,
                "display_name": "MLavrentyev",
                "accept_rate": 83
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1432225903,
            "creation_date": 1432225903,
            "body": "<p>Instead of using <code>.readLine()<\/code> with a <code>BufferedReader<\/code>, use a <code>Scanner<\/code>. This way you can use the <code>.next()<\/code> to get the next thing up to whitespace (any whitespace).<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 30379475,
            "question_id": 30379401
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/26dbb4e470c13ae001a8fd8dd3940d41?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 1797794,
                "user_type": "registered",
